<TITLE> Ershad violated code with motorcade: home minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 30 (bdnews24.com) - Jatiya Party chairman HM Ershad violated the election code of conduct by taking his motorcade to Kurigram-2 ahead of the by-elections, the home minister said on Monday. A local election officer, Nuruzzaman, accused Ershad of violating the election code by campaigning as a sitting MP for his party candidate Golam Habib, Sahara Khatun told parliament on Monday night. Sahara was speaking in reply to an MP's point of order the previous day. JP MP Mujibul Haque Chunnu om Sunday demanded a statement from the home minister on Ershad's motorcade being attacked in Rangpur. Six people were reportedly injured and seven cars damaged as the motorcade was heading for Kurigram. Police said a mob attacked after a youth was run over by a microbus in the motorcade. Chunnu said Sunday Ershad was in hospital after being injured in the attack. The home minister replied Monday: "It is not true. Ershad was not been wounded or in hospital." However, she termed the attack on Ershad's motorcade as "unwarranted and regrettable". "Police have been ordered to arrest those involved as quickly as possible and bring them to justice," she said. Security tightened for Ershad The home minister said Ershad's security had been enhanced during his "tour". Security had been beefed up in all the by-election areas as a result of the incident, she added. Polls campaigns stop at midnight Tuesday All election campaigning comes to an end at Tuesday midnight ahead of the April 2 by-polls in Bogra-6 &7, Rangpur-3 &6, Kurigram-2 and Kishoreganj-6. The movement of vehicles in the election areas will come under restriction and election day will be a holiday in polling areas. b
